  "text": "RGB is the most common color space in video and most of the digital images are also expressed with the RGB color space. However, the spatial structure does not meet the people in subjective judgment of color similarity. So, it is necessary to convert it into HSV space which is closest with the subjective perception of human eyes [CITATION_1] . Each component of HSV color space is quantified as non-equal interval for 8 segments, 3 segments and 3 segments. At the same time, they are synthesized into one-dimensional feature vector [CITATION_2] . The HSV color space can be quantified for 72 segments. Then the histogram distribution is calculated and is defined by:",
