    "7343536": {
      "title": "Skin color enhancement based on favorite skin color in HSV color space",
      "abstract": "Skin color enhancement based on favorite skin color is proposed to make skin color displayed on large screen flat panel TVs agree with human favorite skin color. A robust skin detection method in different intensity is obtained after analyzing the distribution of skin color in HSV color space. The favorite skin color region is found via a psychological experiment too. Then the skin color detected is enhanced with different degrees according to the distance between it and the favorite skin color. The experimental result displayed on 60-inch plasma display panel (PDP) shows that the skin colors detected are approached to the favorite skin color region with different degrees. The skin colors enhanced are more natural and agree with the comprehension of human vision and psychology perceived in advance."
    },
    "124718029": {
      "title": "An image retrieval algorithm based on HSV color segment histograms",
      "abstract": "Aiming at the image retrieval based on color feature,a new image retrieval algorithm based on HSV non-uniform quantization color segment histogram was presented.The basic idea of segment histogram was to divide image space into fixed blocks according to a certain strategy,and then the color histogram of each block was calculated as the color feature of the corresponding block.Users assigned a weight to each block according to the importance of the space information that the block contains,and assigned zero to the unimportant of the block.This algorithm made use of HSV non-uniform quantization and the block of image.It improved the traditional histogram for its lack of space information.Compared with traditional histogram method,the results indicate that the proposed algorithm based on HSV non-uniform quantization color segment histogram has better retrieval precision."
    }
  },
